cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SOC, cs.IR 

This paper deals with social media and political manipulation, which falls under the domain of social media analysis and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper also deals with the spread of disinformation and the identification of malicious content, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also analyzes user behavior and identifies features that are predictive of users who spread malicious content, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
